title: Gossip Girl: Where Are They Now?

json.text: It has been nine years since we were first introduced  to
the beautiful glamorous and talented cast of gossip girl
and four years since we've seen the last episode of the series.
So let's take a look at what the cast
has been up to since then.
Check out the cast of gossip girl is right now right here on Listed.
Can you guys belive it's been four years
since the phrase XOXO has been in our weekly vocabulary
thanks to gossip girl.
I can't either and I don't know about you
but I'm missing seeing the show's ridiculously good-looking cast
all together on a regular basis.
But even though they may not be working together on the show anymore
they've all moved on to great things.
First up who could forget everyone's favorite boy next door
Penn Badgley, who played Dan Humphrey on the show
Penn has been in a few movies sicen his days of being revealed as the gossip girl
but he's mostly been focusing on his band Mother
But he has done a couple of indie movies this year
such as Macaulay Culkin and Adam Green's Aladdin
and a romantic drama the Paper Store.
Up next is another insanely attractive man from the gossip girl world
It's Chase Crowford who played the hunky and sensitive Nate Archibald.
Chase was one of the leads on ABC show Blood and Oil las year
but the show was cancelled after just ten episodes
but don't worry
we could always see Chases's gorgeous base in the baseball dramedy undrafted this summer
and the horror film Eloise later this year.
You know I'm not usually into scary movies but for Chase
I think i'll make an exception
and moving on to the bad boy who eventually showed a secret heart of gold on the show
and proved to be Blair's one true love in the process
it's Ed Westwick  AKA Chuck Bass
Like Chase, Westwick also had an ABC show last year called Wicked City
which was also cancelled.
Hopefully Ed will have better luck with the movies he has coming out
including one thriller called Takedown and another called Jekyll Island.
Hopefully he has to play the bad guy in both because he's very good at that.
Next up we've got Taylor Momsen who played Dan's sister Jenny Humphrey
and of all actors on this list, Taylor might have the biggest transformation so far.
Taylor, like her former fictional bro Penn, has put her acting career on the back burner
to focus on her music with her band the Pretty Reckless.
The band released two albums since 2010 and is currently working on new music.
Taylor had some controversial moments since exiting gossip girl.
and she's opted for a way gothic look these days
but she seems to be staying out of the limelight for now and putting all of her energy into her work.
Probably a smart choice.
Next up is the lovely Jessica Szohr AKA the cool girl next door of gossip girl Vanessa Abrams.
Jessica has done movies as well as TV since her GG days appearing in films like Ted2
and shows like Medical Dramas Complications on USA and MMA inspired drama Kingdom
on the audience network.
She will also have a role in the upcoming reboot of Twin Peaks.
Next up is the adorable little bro turned bona fide Hollywood hunk Connor Paolo
who started asSyrena's brother Eric Vander Woodsen on the show.
Connor left gossip girl and joined the ABC drama Revenge in 2011
where he starts as Declan Porter for two seasons.
He also had a guest starring role on the TV show Rush Hour and he had a role in the indie horror film Like Lambs.
Next up is Leighton Meester who played everyone's favorite Queen B
of the upper east side on gossip girl, Blair Waldorf.
Leighton recently got married to the Oasys Adam Brody in 2014
who she probably fell in love with after they bonded over being former teen icons, right?
A couple gave birth to a daughter named Arlo last year but her love and marriage and baby hiatus
will be coming to an end this year as she set to co-star with Adam Bailey
and foxes upcoming time-traveling comedy Making History
Wow, I cannot wait to see Blair be funny
I  almost can't even imagine it.
And last but never ever least is the actress who played the true heart of Gossip Girl
It's Blake Lively, AKA Serena Vander Woodsen forever in our hearts
Blake made her move from TV to movies with the drama Age of Adeline
and this summer shark attck thriller the Shallows.
She also started a lifestyle websitecalled Preserve but she shut it down in 2015
Blake is of course married to Deadpool himself Mr. Ryan Reynolds
the couple has one daughter named James and recently announced
that they have another baby on the way.
All in all, it's safe to say Serena definitely got her happily ever after with the man of her dreams
at least in real life.
Alright. So now I want to know who you've missed the most out of the Gossip Girl cast
who do you think is going to have the best career of them all
Let me know all your thoughts in the comment sction  below
and after that don't forget to click right over here to check out celebrity relationships
that survived cheating scandals
Thanks so much for hanging out with me here on Listed.
I'm your host Megyn LaMontane and I'll see you guys next time
